@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{orderless-extras.el} extends @samp{orderless}, the completion style that matches candidates against space-separated components in any order. While @samp{orderless} ships with several matching styles (literal, regexp, flex, initialism, and others), activating a particular style for a single component within a query requires a dispatcher function.

This package provides four dispatchers, each triggered by appending a suffix character to a search component:

@multitable {aaaaaa} {aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa} {aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa}
@headitem Suffix
@tab Style
@tab Section
@item @samp{~}
@tab @code{orderless-flex}
@tab @ref{Flex matching}
@item @samp{,}
@tab @code{orderless-initialism}
@tab @ref{Initialism}
@item @samp{;}
@tab @code{orderless-prefixes}
@tab @ref{Prefixes}
@item @samp{!}
@tab @code{orderless-without-literal}
@tab @ref{Exclusion}
@end multitable

To use these dispatchers, add them to the @code{orderless-style-dispatchers} list:

@lisp
(setq orderless-style-dispatchers
      '(orderless-extras-flex-dispatcher
        orderless-extras-initialism-dispatcher
        orderless-extras-prefixes-dispatcher
        orderless-extras-exclusion-dispatcher))
@end lisp

